==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kelvin
<hw>Kel"vin</hw> <pr>(k⟦ecr⟧l"v⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from
Lord <ets>Kelvin</ets>, English physicist.]</ety> <def>The SI unit of
temperature, defined as being 1/273.16 of the triple point of water;
abbreviated <abbr>K</abbr>. The melting point of water at 760 mm
pressure is 273.15 Kelvins, and the boiling point 373.15 Kelvins. One
degree Kelvin is equal to one degree Centigrade, and ⟦frac95⟧ degrees
Fahrenheit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

